si
                </div>
                <p>These conversions allow US contractors to understand and=
 implement mix designs developed using metric standards, ensuring consisten=
t quality across international construction projects.</p>
            </div>
           =20
            <h2>Structural Engineering Load Conversions</h2>
            <p>Structural engineers regularly convert loads, stresses, and =
moments between different unit systems when analyzing buildings, bridges, a=
nd other structures. Building codes may specify loads in different units, a=
nd engineers must ensure all calculations use consistent systems to avoid c=
atastrophic design errors.</p>
